thinking_summary:
Updated the canonical files. The revised `answer.tex` now expands:

- the normal-bidual/support-projection setup for DKEP boundary pieces;
- the finite-boundary criterion, including cut-down normality and compact-corner hypertrace;
- the graph-product meet formula via DKEP correspondence supports plus CDHJKN fusion;
- the relative Bass–Serre paradox membership check \(p,q\in S_{X_B}(N)\).

I compiled `answer.tex` twice with `pdflatex`; it compiles cleanly with no warnings and produces a 5-page PDF.
